{"name": "cadica-data-set", "metadata": {"name": "cadica-data-set", "version": "1.0.1", "classifiers": [], "home_page": null, "license": null, "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": [], "summary": null, "upload_time": 1733803127}, "documentation": ["This is the cadica-data-set repository!\nMore details soon to come on how to install thy package via pip install,\nand use the code/libraries in the package.\n"], "modules": [{"name": "cadica_data_set", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": [{"name": "cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet", "xref": {"fqname": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet", "project": null}}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSetSamplingPolicy", "xref": {"fqname": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSetSamplingPolicy", "project": null}}]}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set", "documentation": [], "functions": [], "variables": [], "classes": [{"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSetSamplingPolicy", "bases": ["Enum"], "methods": [], "class_variables": [{"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSetSamplingPolicy.NONE", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSetSamplingPolicy.BALANCED_SAMPLING", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "instance_variables": [], "inner_classes": [], "documentation": ["Represents the sampling policy to use when returning the training data.\n\nAttributes\n----------\nNONE : int\n    Applies no sampling policy. This will return all labeled lesion/nonlesion images \n    regardless of the class distribution.\nBALANCED_SAMPLING : int\n    Tries to \"evenly\" sample images to return a 50/50 distribution across lesion/nonlesioned images.\n    Use this policy if you don't want your model to \"overfit\" towards lesioned images or nonlesioned images.\n    The CADICA data set has more lesioned images than nonlesioned images. The sampling happens at the \"video level.\""]}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet", "bases": [], "methods": [{"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet.__init__", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Initializes a CadicaDataSet instance.\n\nParameters\n----------\npath : str \n    The absolute path to the CADICA data set folder on your file system", "region Initialization"]}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet.load", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Loads and indexes the CADICA data set into memory from the path supplied\nin the initializer synchronously. This API reads the CADICA data set folder and indexes all\nselected lesioned and nonlesioned images for easy training data generation and\ngeneration of \"labels.\" This API must be called before the get_training_data_image_paths(),\nis_lesioned_image(), and is_nonlesioned_image() API's are invoked. ", "endregion", "region Core Public Methods"]}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet.get_training_data_image_paths", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "sampling_policy", "type": {"name": "CadicaDataSetSamplingPolicy", "xref": {"fqname": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSetSamplingPolicy", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns training data as an array of image paths to all \"lesioned\" and \"nonlesioned\"\nlabeled images in the CADICA data set. This can be used as the training data and validation data\nto train a image model based on these labels. You must provide a sampling_policy and invoke the \nload() API before calling this method.   \n\nParameters\n----------\nsampling_policy : CadicaDataSetSamplingPolicy \n    A sampling policy to use when generating the training data. "]}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet.is_lesioned_image", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "image_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns True if the image_path is classified as a \"lesioned\" image in the CADICA data set.\nThis can be used as a usefel \"labeling\" func during image model training if needed.   \n\nParameters\n----------\nimage_path: The path to the image to \"label\" "]}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet.is_nonlesioned_image", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "image_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Returns True if the image_path is classified as a \"nonlesioned\" image in the CADICA data set.\nThis can be used as a usefel \"labeling\" func during image model training if needed.   \n\nParameters\n----------\nimage_path: The path to the image to \"label\" "]}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet._get_selected_image_frame_file_paths", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "patient_dir", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "video_dir", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "cur_path", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["endregion", "region Private Helpers"]}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet._read_cadica_txt_file", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "file", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "cadica_data_set.cadica_data_set.CadicaDataSet._update_image_paths_for_balanced_sampling", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "self", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "image_paths", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "max_count", "type": null, "default": null}, {